column14: Comments
Email has a link to this site manage ewallet but there is no mention of it on my account dashboard.
Waiting for parents to confirm. They said they requested to have it delivered to them directly but the site is asking for the delivery address again.
Excellent

Last year when we spend our grant money on books, it was a nightmare because we paid with the school's credit card but tax was added to it.  It was an insane ordeal that took over a month to fix.  I live chatted today to ask how me can go about using the credit card for the order but not have tax charged to it.  The agent told me to use combo payment and put the subtotal on the card and the tax on a "check".  Then, I'll have to call once the books are shipped to get the tax removed.  This absolutely blows my mind why using tax exempt is so difficult with Scholastic since you work with tax exempt schools daily.  There has to be a better way.
I would like to be able to support by board books, paperbacks, or hardcovers
I love Scholastic! You are amazing. I have used Scholastic for 20 in Canada and then 18 years in CA, and I have always had positive experiences.

I recently talked to a rep over the phone and had everything on my account settled until I got an outstanding balance on my account due to the company duplicating my orders. When I live chatted with an agent I was told that there was no duplicate order and that they have not received a payment , however today I received the duplicate order and was told yes they could see both orders. One rep told me to write refused on the box and send it back. Today I was told to wait for a return label to print and then send back. I'm very disappointed in the inconsistent advice. Also when I called to correct the problem before it got to this point I was told there was no issue and just if something happened to do it one way. Now I'm told to do it another way. What happened to listening to the customer? If the first rep would have listened to me, this would not have happened but instead argued with me and told me there was no other order.

Pennsylvania's sales tax is 6%, however I noticed on this order (that I wanted to submit before losing February rewards) I was charged more than that - 15%. (Thinking back to my order last month, I believe the tax seemed off to me then as well.) Tonight, when I used my "$10 to spend now" reward, I spent $11, so I was charged $1. With PA's sales tax it totaled $1.06, which was correct. Then, when I used my "$10 to spend in February" reward I received from last month's order, the total was also $11, so I was charged an additional dollar, making my teacher total $2.00. With PA sales tax $2x.06$0.12 which would be a total of $2.12, not the $2.30 I was charged. Now I understand it's only a few cents this time, but if it continues to happen and has happened to possibly hundreds of teachers, that money adds up. There may be a tax explanation that can be shared with me, or perhaps an algorithm is wrong and needs fixed. Thank you for your time.
